Practice Questions

Q1. Apply RANK() based on Salary DESC.
   Return all columns + Rank.
 
 SELECT *,
      RANK() OVER (ORDER BY Salary DESC) AS RankVal 
 FROM Employees;

Q2. Apply DENSE_RANK() based on Salary DESC.
   Return all columns + DenseRank.

  SELECT *, 
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY Salary DESC) AS DenseRankVal 
  FROM Employees;

Q3. Apply RANK() within each Department based on Salary DESC.

  SELECT *, 
       RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY Department ORDER BY Salary DESC) AS RankVal 
  FROM Employees ;

Q4. Apply DENSE_RANK() within each Department based on Salary ASC.

  SELECT *,
         DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY Department ORDER BY Salary ASC) AS DenseRankVal
  FROM Employees ; 

Q5. Show both RANK() and DENSE_RANK() together ordered by Salary DESC.

  SELECT *, 
       RANK() OVER (ORDER BY Salary DESC) AS RankVal, 
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY Salary DESC) AS DenseRankVal 
  FROM Employees ;
